{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> εὐεργετ-έω</b>, <br /> the augment εὐηργ- is sometimes found, especially in codices, as <i>imperfect</i> εὐηργέτουν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Apologia Socratis” 26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> εὐηργέτησα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 835, variant in 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 1.16, but ηὐεργέτησα 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 9.14: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> εὐηργέτηκα variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 140 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> εὐηργέτημαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.2.3, “SIG” 798.5 (Cyzicus, 1st c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], but Inscrr. and Papyrus have εὐεργέτηκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.573 (4th c.BC), εὐεργέτημαι “PLond.” 2.169.26 (1st c.AD), εὐεργετήθην “IG” 7.2808 (Hyettus, 3rd c.AD), ηὐεργετημένοι “PTeb.” 326.16 (3rd c.AD)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be a benefactor</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 670, “IG” 22.786, etc.; [Ἰησοῦς] διῆλθεν -τῶν NT.Act.10.38. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>to be proclaimed as</b> εὐεργέτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.2, “JHS” 10.76 (Patara, 1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>do good services</b> or <b>show kindness to</b> one, τοὺς θανόντας εἰ θέλεις εὐεργετεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 266.1, compare “Eu.” 725, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1540, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator [same place], etc.; ὁ νόμος βούλεται -τεῖν βίον ἀνθρώπων 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 248; εὐ. τὸν δῆμον “IG” 22.791.25, etc.; τὸν θεὸν εὐεργετηκότες “SIG” 417.13 (Delph., 3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> <i>cognate</i>, εὐ. τινὰ τὴν μεγίστην εὐεργεσίαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 36c, compare “R.” 615b; ὅ τι ἂν ἡμᾶς εὐεργετήσῃς [prev. work] 345a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μεγάλως or μεγάλα εὐ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.2.10, 12: with _dative_ _of things_, χρήμασιν εὐ. [prev. work] 2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>have a kindness done one</b>, εὐεργεσίαν εὐεργετηθείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 520c; μείζω εὐηργετημένοι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.2.3; καί τι εὐεργέτηται ὑπ᾽ ἐμοῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 43a; ἀντὶ πολλῶν καὶ μεγάλων ὧν εὐεργετήθη παρὰ τοῦ θεοῦ “IG” 7.2808 (Hyettus, 3rd c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εὐεργετούμενος εἰς χρήματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 184b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2109","accentedUnicode":"εὐεργετέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2110","matchingForm":"εὐεργέτης","stepTransliteration":"euergetēs","gloss":"benefactor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恩主","_es_Gloss":"benefactor","_zh_Gloss":"恩主"}],"shortDef":"to do good to","mediumDef":"to do good to <br /><b>to do good, exercise beneficence,</b> <ref='Act.10.38'>Acts 10:38</ref>*","stepGloss":"to do good","stepTransliteration":"euergeteō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"hacer el bien","_zh_tw_Definition":"行善, 澤及 (徒10:38)","_zh_Definition":"行善, 泽及 (徒10:38)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"làm việc tốt; làm việc thiện; làm phước","_zh_tw_Gloss":"行善","_es_Gloss":"hacer el bien","_zh_Gloss":"行善"}]}